Developed as part of a Computer Science thesis (TCC) at Universidade Tiradentes
(UNIT), 2026, advised by Yuri Faro Dantas de Sant'Anna. It investigates whether
Lafont's Interaction Combinators (1997) can serve as a formal model for
deterministic distributed reduction in Grid Computing.

If you use Relativist in academic work, a citation to the thesis is appreciated.
